<div id="does-instagram-ad-copy-matter"></div>
<h2>Why does Instagram ad copy matter?</h2>
<p>Instagram is primarily a visual platform, so it‚Äôs easy to wonder why you should be <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/19/copywriting-skills" target="_blank" rel="noopener">spending time improving your copywriting</a> rather than focusing on your videos, photos, and graphics.</p>
<p>Well, <a href="https://blog.hootsuite.com/long-instagram-captions-experiment/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">a study</a> on the impact of Instagram caption length found that a longer caption directly correlated with more engagement. This is in organic posts, rather than ads. But it goes to show that even on a platform dominated by visuals, your copy matters.</p>
<p>In terms of Instagram ads specifically, it&#8217;s also<a href="https://www.brafton.com/blog/social-media/social-advertising-benchmarks/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> been found</a> that in-feed ads perform better than Stories ads. They found that the click-through rate (CTR) for feed ads on Instagram ranges between 0.22% and 0.88%, and the CTR for Stories ads varies between 0.33% and 0.54%. A big difference between in-feed and Stories ads? The copy requirements.</p>
<p>Still, users report that Instagram Stories with a narrative including photos, videos, and text are the most appealing‚Äîand the most likely to get them to keep clicking through.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-chart.webp" alt="instagram ad copy - chart of converting instagram stories" width="664" height="429" class="aligncenter wp-image-85229 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-chart.webp 664w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-chart-480x310.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 664px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/instagram-story-formats" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Source</em></a></p>
<p>The bottom line? Spending time writing <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/instagram-advertising" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram ads</a> is worth it‚Äîand can help with your conversion numbers.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <strong>Looking for more data on the average performance of Meta ads in your industry?</strong> Download our latest <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/facebook-benchmarks?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_FBAdsBenchmarks2024_Download" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2024 Facebook Ads Benchmarks Report </a>for free here!</p>
<div id="instagram-ad-copy-tips"></div>
<h2>12 tips for writing high-converting Instagram ad copy</h2>
<p>Here&#8217;s how you can start writing <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/07/13/instagram-best-practices" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram ads that guarantee increased conversion rates</a> for your business.</p>
<h3>1. Stick to Instagram ad guidelines</h3>
<p>The first step to writing Instagram <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/01/03/ad-copy-examples" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ad copy that converts</a> is sticking to the guidelines. There‚Äôs no sense wasting your time writing a quippy narrative description that‚Äôs going to get cut off before the product is mentioned‚Äîor, say, name-dropping that celebrity if it isn‚Äôt going to make the strict character limit and grab some eyes in the feed.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-name-drop.webp" alt="instagram ad copy example - cuddle and kind" width="402" height="604" class="aligncenter wp-image-85231 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-name-drop.webp 402w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/instagram-ad-copy-name-drop-200x300.webp 200w" sizes="(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://cuddleandkind.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Cuddle + Kind</em></a><em> makes sure Jessica Alba is visible in that copy. </em></p>
<p>Here‚Äôs an overview of the character limits to keep in mind for your Instagram ad copy.</p>
<table width="624">
<tbody>
<tr>
